                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t17751206-25-defend547 t17751206-25-deflabel106"></join>, not having the fear of God before his eyes, but <rs id="t17751206-25-off107" type="offenceDescription">
                     <interp inst="t17751206-25-off107" type="offenceCategory" value="kill"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17751206-25-off107" type="offenceSubcategory" value="murder"></interp>
               being moved and seduced by the instigation of the Devil, on the <rs id="t17751206-25-cd108" type="crimeDate">4th day of September, in the thirteenth year of the reign of our sovereign lord George the Third</rs>
                     <join result="offenceCrimeDate" targOrder="Y" targets="t17751206-25-off107 t17751206-25-cd108"></join>, by the grace of God, king of Great Britain, France, and Ireland, defender of the faith, and so forth, with force and arms, at the Cape of Good Hope, on the coast of Africa, in parts beyond the seas without England, feloniously, wilfully, and of his malice aforethought, did make an assault upon 
